# Massachusetts Design System Color Palette

All colors in GrantWell must come from the official MDS palette. No exceptions.

## Brand Colors

### Bay Blue (Primary)

| State    | Hex       | CSS Variable                  |
|----------|-----------|-------------------------------|
| Default  | `#14558F` | `var(--mds-color-bay-blue)`   |
| Hover    | `#104472` | `var(--mds-color-bay-blue-hover)` |
| Active   | `#0A2B48` | `var(--mds-color-bay-blue-active)` |
| Disabled | `#F0F0F0` | `var(--mds-color-disabled-bg)` |

### Berkshires Green (Accent)

| State    | Hex       | CSS Variable                        |
|----------|-----------|-------------------------------------|
| Default  | `#388557` | `var(--mds-color-berkshires-green)`  |
| Hover    | `#32784E` | `var(--mds-color-berkshires-green-hover)` |
| Active   | `#275D3D` | (inline OK for rare use)            |

### Other Brand Colors

- **Duckling Yellow** `#F6C51B` -- highlight only, use sparingly
- **Independence Cranberry** `#680A1D` -- decorative graphics only, never for interactive elements
- **Granite Gray** `#535353` -- neutral backgrounds for contrast

## Utility Colors (System States Only)

| Purpose  | Hex       | CSS Variable              | Use For                    |
|----------|-----------|---------------------------|----------------------------|
| Success  | `#24A850` | `var(--mds-color-success)` | Confirmations, completed   |
| Warning  | `#F6B622` | `var(--mds-color-warning)` | Caution, incomplete        |
| Danger   | `#CD0D0D` | `var(--mds-color-danger)`  | Errors, destructive actions|
| Focus    | `#0088FF` | `var(--mds-color-focus-light)` | Focus rings on light bg |
| Focus    | `#B2DBFF` | `var(--mds-color-focus-dark)`  | Focus rings on dark bg  |

## Semantic Aliases

Use these for most code -- they map to the brand colors above:

```css
var(--mds-color-primary)        /* Bay Blue #14558F */
var(--mds-color-primary-hover)  /* #104472 */
var(--mds-color-primary-active) /* #0A2B48 */
var(--mds-color-primary-light)  /* #f2f8fd */
var(--mds-color-accent)         /* Berkshires Green #388557 */
var(--mds-color-text)           /* #333333 */
var(--mds-color-text-secondary) /* #5a5a5a */
var(--mds-color-heading)        /* #0a2e52 */
var(--mds-color-background)     /* #f9fafb */
var(--mds-color-border)         /* #e2e8f0 */
var(--mds-color-white)          /* #ffffff */
```

## Rules

1. **NEVER hard-code hex colors in components.** Always use `var(--mds-color-*)` in CSS or import from `components/ui/styles.ts` in JS/TS
2. **NEVER invent new colors.** If a design needs a color not listed above, raise it for review
3. **NEVER use Cloudscape tokens** (`awsui.$*`). They are being removed from the project
4. **Disabled states:** background `#F0F0F0`, text `#707070`
5. **Focus indicators:** always `#0088FF` on light backgrounds, `#B2DBFF` on dark backgrounds
6. **Utility colors are semantic** -- never use Success Green decoratively, only for success states

```tsx
// Bad
<button style={{ backgroundColor: "#14558F" }}>Submit</button>

// Good (CSS class)
<button className="btn-primary">Submit</button>

// Good (CSS variable in stylesheet)
.btn-primary { background-color: var(--mds-color-primary); }

// Good (JS import)
import { colors } from "@/components/ui/styles";
<button style={{ backgroundColor: colors.primary }}>Submit</button>
```
